cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.RO. 

The paper focuses on face alignment, which is a computer vision problem, and uses machine learning techniques such as regression forests and feature extraction. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The use of K-cluster Regression Forests and Affine Pose Regression also suggests that the paper may fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the use of Pyramid Histogram of Oriented Gradients (PHOG) features suggests that the paper may also fall under cs.MM (Multimedia) as PHOG is commonly used in multimedia applications. Finally, the use of 3D-APR suggests that the paper may also fall under cs.RO (Robotics) as 3D transformations are commonly used in robotics applications.
